{"note":"Malaga. Hello today we got up a little bit early. Had breakfast got off the ship which was docked right in the heart of everything so we got off the boat and we’re right in the middle of Malaga, which was nice and then we just crossed the street, walked through the park and went to. I believe it’s called Alcon Terra Alcântara one word that sucks there. It is Al Cantera so we did that and spent a lot of time up there. There was a lot to see. I don’t know if we even saw it all. I think we did then we came out of there and we went down into the city and tried to find the Picasso museum, beautiful city. Everything is beautiful here sat down by the Picasso museum for tapas and beer and I have the best in Salato Russo. I’ve had ever Satish had the omelette potato egg omelette thing. I forget what it’s called and with the aïoli and then we jumped into the line made a nice older couple from our floor here on the Oceana Anya, who didn’t have tickets to teach she helped them get tickets and then we went in and spent a lot of time in the Picasso museum, which was pretty amazing and do a shopping in the gift shop sat down in the café there for a minute and then went out, went to the cathedral, which was like huge very impressive. A little overwhelming after everything else we’ve seen I got a little tired there, but I mean like crazy impressive cathedral, and then got out of there went to another spot had a bone in Vegas and some kind of hormone croquette, sort of thing and some sangria and walk to Bankinter to try to use her ATM, which didn’t work met some older couple from San Francisco were interesting and then now we’re back on the boat we’re supposed to have cocktails with Sachin and his wife which may or may not happen and that’s all for now better\n\nwe got up the ship and as soon as we got off, it was an amazing site. We saw that the city is so beautiful and people were also beautiful. They were all dressed really well. Everything was immaculate and beautiful. The architecture was amazing. We just walked a few steps outside the cruise and there was a big park and walkway and there was so many people walking going to work so the cruise terminal is a part of the is not really far from where people actually work and go to work so we walk slowly towards the fort or whatever the old Alize and then soaked in all the sun and decides Felicity then after an hour, we climb down around one 1130. It was time to go to the Picasso museum. We stopped outside had a wonderful meals as we waited in the line we saw the there was a couple From our own same ship, which, or waiting in the line to get into the museum without any tickets and then we happen to start talking to them and ended up helping them in buying the tickets for the 2 PM slot, which were the last two tickets available for the day and that was a great experience. The Picasso museum is amazing. The creation is even better. I have seen so many Picasso museums, but there was nothing like this. It is very limited in the sense it’s not going on and on on it’s a smaller building compared to many other buildings in Paris and states yet it has Pat with every phase of his life and the most critical artwork that he created so those who are into the classical classical. So modern art not classical you got to see this, it’s not very crowded because the tickets are limited so from there we came out. I wonderful lunch at a restaurant that was recommended by Claude and it was really good. Then we walked out. They talked about other things and now we are back in the ship that’s it\n\n\nPic 1 2 3 are from the Picassos malaga musrum ","bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":1}